Defendant Jeffery C Bates in court with Attorney Hazel Jean Washington.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter here for plea/sentencing.  AS TO PLEA:  AS TO COUNT #1:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty.  Judgment of conviction entered.

AS TO COUNTS #2 AND #3:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered charges dismissed and read-in for the purposes of sentencing.

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess any gun or other firearms. 
Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  AS TO COUNT #1:  The Court imposed the following sentence:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be FOUR (4) years consecutive to any other sentence.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for TWO (2) years with credit for SEVEN (7) days time served.  Defendant shall serve TWO (2) years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The Court STAYS sentence and orders PROBATION for TWO (2) years.

The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program;
The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Random urine screens to ensure compliance;
 - SIX (6) month condition time in the House of Correction--GOOD TIME--CONSECUTIVE;
 - Pay $600 fine;
 - Operating privileges suspended for THREE (3) years to commence upon eligibility to reinstate license;
 - Interlock device for THREE (3) years.
 - Cooperate and participate in the Mandatory Intoxicated Driver Assessment and Driver Safety Plan;
 - Court ordered that the $2,500 bail on deposit be returned to surety;
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements by the end of probationary period.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.

Filed,
